How to Build
============
Requirements:
*) libserializer (it can be found:http://hysoftware.net/softview.htm?type=software&file=/settings/software/simple_serializer.json)
*) GNU/Linux or BSD.
*) coreutils
*) gcc-4.8
*) cmake
*) make
*) Qt5 or later. I recommend to install all features. I'll implement new feature in the feature.

Optional:
*) Lua (This hasn't been used yet. But, there is a replacement plan from C++ Based Plugin Loader to Lua)

Instruction:
1) Open your fevorite terminal.
2) $> cd path/to/watcher
3) $> mkdir build&&cd build
4) $> cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX="/path/to/install" ..
    Note: additional cmake option is written at CMakeLists.txt on root source directory.
5) $> make
    Note: To reduce building time, use -jN (N=number of processors.)
6) $> make install
    Note: If you want to install the software into a specific directory, use DESTDIR="/path/to/install"
7) $> cp -r plugins ~/watcher
8) $> cp -r themes  ~/watcher
9) All done. you can run watcher.

If you found instruction issues, post a ticket.

